sql:
SELECT AVG(metric_value) AS average_income
FROM city_metrics
WHERE city_id = 1 AND metric_name = 'average income';

SELECT COUNT(city_id) AS InterestCities
FROM city_keywords
WHERE repetition_count > 50;

external_knowledge:
- "basking in the glory" refers to cities achieving their peak values in metrics;
- "highest achievements" and "shining metrics" metaphorically indicate the maximum metric value recorded for each city;
- "dazzling values" symbolically represents the highest metric_value for each city.

sql:
SELECT log_id, access_time, status_code
FROM city_access_logs
WHERE access_type = 'view' AND status_code = 200;

external_knowledge:
- "Ocean" and "whispered interests" metaphorically refer to the extensive data on cities and their associated keywords; 
- "Mother countries" symbolically represents the countries to which the cities belong; 
- "Average frequency of murmurs" is a metaphorical way to describe the average repetition count of keywords related to each city.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT city_access_logs.user_id) 
FROM city_access_logs 
WHERE city_access_logs.ip_address = 'specific_ip_address';
